description: Manx 3D-printer and laser cutter owners have joined forces to make face shields for health workers.
title: Coronavirus: 3D-printed visors for Manx health workers
title_page: Coronavirus: 3D-printed visors for Manx health workers - BBC News
maintext: Crowd Shield estimates it can make more than 100 face shields a day and the finished products will go into the government's existing supply chain as part of a "contingency plan should the island's front-line workers need" them.
